		"Wizardry: Proving Grounds of the Mad Overlord
	]em
	" is an early role-playing game that was developed for the Apple II and was ported to numerous systems, including the Commodore 64, PC-98, NES, and Game Boy Color. It later received a remake for modern PCs and the Nintendo Switch. Being one of the first role-playihg video games, it codified many of the mechanics and tropes that are well known in the genre. You create a party of customized characters and from there you explore a dungeon in search of treasures and an evil wizard named Werdna, whose amulet you seek.
